@namespace MindAttic.Ideas.Page.HelloWorld
@inherits PageBase
@attribute [Uses(ContentKind.Plugin, "tooltip", 1)]
@attribute [Uses(ContentKind.Control, "textbox", 1)]

@* ============================================================================================
   MindAttic.Ideas.Page.HelloWorld.V1 — the reference modular page.

   Identity is convention: namespace tail "HelloWorld" => key "helloworld", class "V1" => version 1.
   It composes content from OTHER packages with ZERO compile-time reference to them:
     • THEME   — chosen by ThemeKey in data/page.json ("cyberspace"); the host wraps this body in it.
     • COMPONENT/CONTROL — placed by <CmsInclude Ref="..."/>, resolved from the global catalog at runtime.
   [Uses(...)] above declares those string ids so the host hoists their css/js into <head> and
   reference-guards them against deletion. A missing/disabled reference degrades to a placeholder — never
   a crash.
   ============================================================================================ *@

<section class="hello">
    <h1>Hello, world.</h1>
    <p>
        This page is a compiled <code>.razor</code> shipped as a <code>.idea</code>. It references the
        Cyberspace theme and the Tooltip component <strong>by string id</strong> — neither is bundled with
        it, neither is referenced at compile time.
    </p>

    @* Switch ON the tooltip capability (loads its css/js); thereafter any data-tooltip element works. *@
    <CmsInclude Ref="MindAttic.Ideas.Plugin.Tooltip.V1" />
    <p><button type="button" data-tooltip="Resolved at runtime by string id — not compiled in.">Hover me</button></p>

    @* Place an atomic Control by string id; unmatched attributes flow straight through to it. *@
    <p><CmsInclude Ref="MindAttic.Ideas.Control.Textbox.V1" placeholder="Type here…" /></p>
</section>

<style>
    .hello { padding: 2rem; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; }
    .hello h1 { color: var(--ma-ideas-accent, #ff8c00); }
</style>
